The elementary school student animatedly recounts the experience inside a moving car, presumably on his way home from school.

'It's mixed up in my head and my heart,' he continues. 'When she kisses me, it goes to my brain. It goes to my heart.'

Griffin puts his hand on his head as he tries to describe the stream of emotions he had felt during the sweet moment.

'It just goes in my brain so much; it just goes kablooey! It’s so good! I had a funny feeling. It was so great.'

